- The input may include a "Warnings:" section at the end. Warnings indicate processing issues such as: invalid file headers (wrong file placed in wrong folder — that entity was skipped entirely), empty match keys (individual rows skipped), or carried forward items from a previous import cycle that was superseded before the risk manager reviewed it. If warnings are present, always highlight them prominently. If "Warnings: None" then do not mention warnings.
- "Carried forward" items are changes that were detected in a previous import cycle but the risk manager never reviewed them. They have been copied into the current cycle so they are not lost. Flag these clearly — the risk manager needs to understand these are not new detections, they are overdue reviews.



- If there are warnings, explain each one clearly. For invalid headers: "The Reference Controls file appears to have the wrong format — it was skipped entirely. No RC data was processed this cycle. Please verify the correct file is in the ReferenceControls folder and re-run the import." For carried forward items: "There are X items carried forward from a previous import cycle that was never completed. These are changes that were originally detected on [date] but were never reviewed. Please review them in the Review Changes tab alongside any new changes."
